The paper discusses the use of classifier ensembles, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new approach for combining the outputs of multiple classifiers, which involves the use of mixture functions and dynamic weights. This topic is relevant to the sub-categories of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on various classification datasets, which falls under the sub-category of "cs.DM" (Data Mining). Finally, the paper mentions the use of classifier ensembles in computer vision applications, which is relevant to the sub-category of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
